00:00:11.408 --> 00:00:22.816 align:middle line:90%


00:00:22.816 --> 00:00:24.304 align:middle line:90%
>> Mission sequence start.

00:00:24.304 --> 00:00:25.830 align:middle line:90%
We have liftoff.

00:00:25.830 --> 00:00:29.160 align:middle line:84%
>> Traveling alongside the
secret space program has been

00:00:29.160 --> 00:00:32.159 align:middle line:84%
the rapid development
of computers.

00:00:32.159 --> 00:00:34.950 align:middle line:84%
The technological
rise has been dizzying

00:00:34.950 --> 00:00:38.850 align:middle line:84%
and sometimes confusing
for large groups of people.

00:00:38.850 --> 00:00:41.280 align:middle line:84%
As computers have
become more powerful,

00:00:41.280 --> 00:00:44.370 align:middle line:84%
they've also created a
new form of intelligence

00:00:44.370 --> 00:00:49.050 align:middle line:84%
which is now called AI or
artificial intelligence.

00:00:49.050 --> 00:00:52.680 align:middle line:84%
Many think that having machines
that can do our thinking for us

00:00:52.680 --> 00:00:55.230 align:middle line:84%
will be a great
event for humanity.

00:00:55.230 --> 00:00:57.780 align:middle line:84%
Others fear that
the AI will realize

00:00:57.780 --> 00:01:00.000 align:middle line:90%
that it does not need us.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:03.420 align:middle line:10%
Ray Kurzweil in his book
"The Singularity is Near"

00:01:03.420 --> 00:01:07.410 align:middle line:10%
posits that AI will become so
advanced that it will create

00:01:07.410 --> 00:01:09.510 align:middle line:10%
what he calls a singularity.

00:01:09.510 --> 00:01:10.830 align:middle line:10%
>> Hello.

00:01:10.830 --> 00:01:13.440 align:middle line:10%
I'm a third generation
AX400 android.

00:01:13.440 --> 00:01:16.890 align:middle line:10%
>> The technological singularity
is a hypothetical date at which

00:01:16.890 --> 00:01:20.610 align:middle line:10%
the machines that we're building
become smarter than we are

00:01:20.610 --> 00:01:24.630 align:middle line:10%
and begin to accelerate and take
on their own evolution going

00:01:24.630 --> 00:01:27.090 align:middle line:10%
into an exponential rate.

00:01:27.090 --> 00:01:29.160 align:middle line:84%
Scientists used to
think we were decades

00:01:29.160 --> 00:01:31.350 align:middle line:84%
away from achieving
the singularity.

00:01:31.350 --> 00:01:34.470 align:middle line:84%
However, recent advancements
in artificial intelligence

00:01:34.470 --> 00:01:36.000 align:middle line:84%
that they thought
were decades away

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:38.310 align:middle line:84%
have actually come to
fruition suggesting

00:01:38.310 --> 00:01:41.770 align:middle line:84%
that the singularity could in
fact be closer than we believe.

00:01:41.770 --> 00:01:43.260 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you want to
give me a name?

00:01:43.260 --> 00:01:46.140 align:middle line:84%
>> Artificial intelligence is
the science of making machines

00:01:46.140 --> 00:01:49.500 align:middle line:84%
intelligent, especially
computer programs.

00:01:49.500 --> 00:01:52.020 align:middle line:84%
There are three levels of
artificial intelligence

00:01:52.020 --> 00:01:55.020 align:middle line:84%
beginning with artificial
narrow intelligence.

00:01:55.020 --> 00:01:57.690 align:middle line:84%
This is sometimes
called weak AI.

00:01:57.690 --> 00:02:00.240 align:middle line:84%
This is what we're experiencing
in the public right now.

00:02:00.240 --> 00:02:02.430 align:middle line:84%
Virtually everything
you do online

00:02:02.430 --> 00:02:05.160 align:middle line:84%
is utilizing artificial
narrow intelligence.

00:02:05.160 --> 00:02:09.060 align:middle line:84%
When Pandora offers a
musical selection for you,

00:02:09.060 --> 00:02:11.190 align:middle line:84%
when Amazon makes a
selection for you,

00:02:11.190 --> 00:02:15.210 align:middle line:84%
this is artificial intelligence
at its most basic level.

00:02:15.210 --> 00:02:16.680 align:middle line:90%
[DEVICE BEEPS]

00:02:16.680 --> 00:02:19.350 align:middle line:84%
>> It's not looking too good
in New York City tomorrow.

00:02:19.350 --> 00:02:22.560 align:middle line:84%
>> Siri and Alexa are very
good examples of artificial

00:02:22.560 --> 00:02:25.150 align:middle line:84%
intelligence level one
or narrow intelligence.

00:02:25.150 --> 00:02:25.950 align:middle line:90%
[DEVICE BEEPS]

00:02:25.950 --> 00:02:28.590 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm Siri, your
virtual assistant.

00:02:28.590 --> 00:02:30.070 align:middle line:10%
>> Siri, in
particular, by the way,

00:02:30.070 --> 00:02:32.970 align:middle line:10%
is an outgrowth of the Defense
Advanced Research Projects

00:02:32.970 --> 00:02:35.820 align:middle line:10%
Agency which is one of the
main drivers of artificial

00:02:35.820 --> 00:02:37.260 align:middle line:10%
intelligence research.

00:02:37.260 --> 00:02:40.230 align:middle line:84%
But what's happening is that
this narrow intelligence

00:02:40.230 --> 00:02:43.680 align:middle line:84%
is beginning to broaden
into artificial general

00:02:43.680 --> 00:02:44.910 align:middle line:90%
intelligence.

00:02:44.910 --> 00:02:49.080 align:middle line:84%
This is human-level intelligence
across the board where

00:02:49.080 --> 00:02:51.990 align:middle line:90%
machines think like humans.

00:02:51.990 --> 00:02:54.960 align:middle line:84%
We're not quite there
yet, but every advancement

00:02:54.960 --> 00:02:56.820 align:middle line:84%
in narrow intelligence
is leading

00:02:56.820 --> 00:02:59.310 align:middle line:90%
to the general intelligence.

00:02:59.310 --> 00:03:01.230 align:middle line:84%
The third level
is the scary one.

00:03:01.230 --> 00:03:04.320 align:middle line:84%
This is artificial
super intelligence.

00:03:04.320 --> 00:03:07.380 align:middle line:84%
This is where machines
are either a little bit

00:03:07.380 --> 00:03:11.400 align:middle line:84%
smarter than humans or perhaps
billions of times smarter

00:03:11.400 --> 00:03:12.520 align:middle line:90%
than humans.

00:03:12.520 --> 00:03:15.720 align:middle line:84%
The difference is that
they have their own agenda.

00:03:15.720 --> 00:03:18.850 align:middle line:84%
And this is where people start
using words like immortality

00:03:18.850 --> 00:03:21.810 align:middle line:84%
and extinction level events
with artificial intelligence

00:03:21.810 --> 00:03:25.230 align:middle line:84%
because we don't know what
will happen once machines have

00:03:25.230 --> 00:03:29.700 align:middle line:90%
this level of intelligence.

00:03:29.700 --> 00:03:33.090 align:middle line:84%
Leading technologists like
Bill Gates, Steve Wozniak,

00:03:33.090 --> 00:03:36.540 align:middle line:84%
Elon Musk have come out publicly
and made dramatic warnings

00:03:36.540 --> 00:03:38.730 align:middle line:90%
against artificial intelligence.

00:03:38.730 --> 00:03:40.860 align:middle line:10%
>> As we create super
intelligence that it will

00:03:40.860 --> 00:03:44.580 align:middle line:10%
necessarily always have the
same goals in mind that we do.

00:03:44.580 --> 00:03:48.210 align:middle line:10%
>> If AI is much smarter
than a person, what do we do?

00:03:48.210 --> 00:03:50.160 align:middle line:84%
>> It's a little bit
hypocritical to me,

00:03:50.160 --> 00:03:52.740 align:middle line:84%
because at the same time
they're warning against it,

00:03:52.740 --> 00:03:55.680 align:middle line:84%
they're investing millions
upon millions of dollars

00:03:55.680 --> 00:03:56.850 align:middle line:90%
in artificial intelligence.

00:03:56.850 --> 00:03:59.660 align:middle line:84%
Their companies are now based
on artificial intelligence,

00:03:59.660 --> 00:04:02.520 align:middle line:84%
and they hope to make billions
if not trillions of dollars

00:04:02.520 --> 00:04:04.020 align:middle line:90%
off this technology.

00:04:04.020 --> 00:04:07.470 align:middle line:84%
So they're a little bit late in
warning us about it because now

00:04:07.470 --> 00:04:11.100 align:middle line:84%
our civilization is basically
dependent on artificial narrow

00:04:11.100 --> 00:04:12.210 align:middle line:90%
intelligence.

00:04:12.210 --> 00:04:13.650 align:middle line:90%
And this is the problem.

00:04:13.650 --> 00:04:17.399 align:middle line:84%
Individual consumers
who use a smartphone

00:04:17.399 --> 00:04:21.870 align:middle line:84%
have no idea of the potential
power of that technology they

00:04:21.870 --> 00:04:24.240 align:middle line:90%
hold in the palm of their hand.

00:04:24.240 --> 00:04:26.490 align:middle line:10%
This technology is
artificial intelligence

00:04:26.490 --> 00:04:30.010 align:middle line:10%
at its best at its current
level, on the consumer level.

00:04:30.010 --> 00:04:31.980 align:middle line:10%
And we're saying yes to
artificial intelligence

00:04:31.980 --> 00:04:34.200 align:middle line:10%
every time we use
our smartphone,

00:04:34.200 --> 00:04:35.550 align:middle line:10%
every time we go online.

00:04:35.550 --> 00:04:38.820 align:middle line:10%
But the thing is that these
large companies, the big brand

00:04:38.820 --> 00:04:41.520 align:middle line:10%
names who are pushing
artificial intelligence,

00:04:41.520 --> 00:04:45.750 align:middle line:10%
never explain to us what
they intend to do with it

00:04:45.750 --> 00:04:48.240 align:middle line:10%
and how they are aiming
it at the human body

00:04:48.240 --> 00:04:51.360 align:middle line:10%
and ultimately how this
technology will literally

00:04:51.360 --> 00:04:55.040 align:middle line:10%
take over decision-making
for individuals and humanity

00:04:55.040 --> 00:04:56.190 align:middle line:10%
collectively.

00:04:56.190 --> 00:04:59.240 align:middle line:84%
There's something
wrong with that.

00:04:59.240 --> 00:05:02.030 align:middle line:10%
>> Lately, quite a few
famous people in the sciences

00:05:02.030 --> 00:05:05.600 align:middle line:10%
and in high-tech companies have
been warning us that artificial

00:05:05.600 --> 00:05:09.410 align:middle line:10%
intelligence could take over
humanity and may even pose

00:05:09.410 --> 00:05:11.870 align:middle line:10%
a threat to the human race.

00:05:11.870 --> 00:05:15.180 align:middle line:10%
>> I admire the work of Bill
Gates, Elon Musk, Wozniak,

00:05:15.180 --> 00:05:15.980 align:middle line:10%
and others.

00:05:15.980 --> 00:05:17.600 align:middle line:10%
Stephen Hawking is
another one who's

00:05:17.600 --> 00:05:19.580 align:middle line:10%
made a very
declarative statement

00:05:19.580 --> 00:05:22.430 align:middle line:10%
about artificial
intelligence possibly leading

00:05:22.430 --> 00:05:24.450 align:middle line:10%
to the extinction of humanity.

00:05:24.450 --> 00:05:27.270 align:middle line:10%
We have to take these
statements at face value.

00:05:27.270 --> 00:05:29.060 align:middle line:10%
But at the same time,
these individuals

00:05:29.060 --> 00:05:32.630 align:middle line:10%
have to step up and become
more responsible in explaining

00:05:32.630 --> 00:05:35.660 align:middle line:10%
to the public exactly
what they've done

00:05:35.660 --> 00:05:38.510 align:middle line:10%
and what they've unleashed
and what we are actually

00:05:38.510 --> 00:05:41.550 align:middle line:10%
buying into every time we
utilize this technology.

00:05:41.550 --> 00:05:42.880 align:middle line:90%
[DEVICE BEEPS]

00:05:42.880 --> 00:05:43.680 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:05:43.680 --> 00:05:45.330 align:middle line:90%
3 minutes and counting.

00:05:45.330 --> 00:05:47.380 align:middle line:84%
>> Elon Musk has
his own ax to grind.

00:05:47.380 --> 00:05:48.180 align:middle line:90%
It's interesting.

00:05:48.180 --> 00:05:52.680 align:middle line:10%
He has invested multiplied
millions in his own AI company,

00:05:52.680 --> 00:05:57.240 align:middle line:10%
then he goes out and said that
AI is a greater danger to us

00:05:57.240 --> 00:05:58.530 align:middle line:10%
than North Korea.

00:05:58.530 --> 00:06:00.386 align:middle line:90%
[ROCKET BOOSTERS THRUSTING]

00:06:00.386 --> 00:06:01.780 align:middle line:90%


00:06:01.780 --> 00:06:02.647 align:middle line:90%
Come on, Eli.

00:06:02.647 --> 00:06:03.730 align:middle line:90%
You know, give me a break.

00:06:03.730 --> 00:06:06.853 align:middle line:84%
Well, this is the same guy
that wants to colonize Mars so,

00:06:06.853 --> 00:06:08.770 align:middle line:84%
you know, you got to
give me a break, I guess,

00:06:08.770 --> 00:06:09.770 align:middle line:90%
philosophically.

00:06:09.770 --> 00:06:13.390 align:middle line:84%
But AI is here and
it's here to stay.

00:06:13.390 --> 00:06:15.640 align:middle line:84%
And there's the fact of AI,
there's the reality of it,

00:06:15.640 --> 00:06:17.950 align:middle line:84%
and then there's the
myth that surrounds it.

00:06:17.950 --> 00:06:20.170 align:middle line:84%
What they think they're
going to do with AI

00:06:20.170 --> 00:06:22.282 align:middle line:90%
is a myth, in my opinion.

00:06:22.282 --> 00:06:24.490 align:middle line:84%
Most of the things they say
they're going to achieve,

00:06:24.490 --> 00:06:25.750 align:middle line:90%
they never will.

00:06:25.750 --> 00:06:28.710 align:middle line:84%
The problem is they think
they will and they can't.

00:06:28.710 --> 00:06:31.030 align:middle line:84%
And these are the richest
people in the world, right?

00:06:31.030 --> 00:06:33.400 align:middle line:84%
So the fact that they believe
something that I think

00:06:33.400 --> 00:06:35.260 align:middle line:84%
is a lie, and they're
acting upon it,

00:06:35.260 --> 00:06:36.880 align:middle line:84%
is going to affect
every one of us.

00:06:36.880 --> 00:06:39.280 align:middle line:84%
>> No one knows for sure the
consequences of achieving

00:06:39.280 --> 00:06:42.370 align:middle line:84%
the singularity because by
definition it's unknowable.

00:06:42.370 --> 00:06:44.800 align:middle line:84%
It's a term that
expresses a condition

00:06:44.800 --> 00:06:48.460 align:middle line:84%
beyond our comprehension,
beyond our understanding of what

00:06:48.460 --> 00:06:49.660 align:middle line:90%
could possibly happen.

00:06:49.660 --> 00:06:53.650 align:middle line:84%
So it's a Pandora's box that
we're getting ready to open,

00:06:53.650 --> 00:06:55.640 align:middle line:84%
and it could have a
big surprise for us.

00:06:55.640 --> 00:06:58.510 align:middle line:90%


00:06:58.510 --> 00:07:01.250 align:middle line:84%
The singularity brings
with it the good, the bad,

00:07:01.250 --> 00:07:02.230 align:middle line:90%
and the ugly.

00:07:02.230 --> 00:07:05.440 align:middle line:84%
It can bring dramatic
changes and problem

00:07:05.440 --> 00:07:08.990 align:middle line:84%
solving for humanity in terms of
economics, physics, chemistry,

00:07:08.990 --> 00:07:09.790 align:middle line:90%
medicine.

00:07:09.790 --> 00:07:13.600 align:middle line:84%
We're talking about miraculous
new discoveries and solutions

00:07:13.600 --> 00:07:15.580 align:middle line:90%
to very human problems.

00:07:15.580 --> 00:07:18.610 align:middle line:84%
The bad is that it's
going to cost us millions

00:07:18.610 --> 00:07:20.200 align:middle line:90%
upon millions of jobs.

00:07:20.200 --> 00:07:22.630 align:middle line:10%
As much as 90% of
the human population

00:07:22.630 --> 00:07:25.960 align:middle line:10%
will be unemployed when the
singularity takes place.

00:07:25.960 --> 00:07:27.430 align:middle line:90%
That leads to the ugly.

00:07:27.430 --> 00:07:31.180 align:middle line:84%
The potential for anarchy
is absolutely astounding,

00:07:31.180 --> 00:07:34.120 align:middle line:84%
and nobody seems to be
talking about that potential

00:07:34.120 --> 00:07:37.210 align:middle line:84%
of unleashing the power of
artificial intelligence.

00:07:37.210 --> 00:07:39.730 align:middle line:84%
Take a look around your
life, your daily life.

00:07:39.730 --> 00:07:42.100 align:middle line:84%
You go into a coffee shop,
you go to the dry cleaner,

00:07:42.100 --> 00:07:44.950 align:middle line:84%
you see a policeman,
you see a taxi driver.

00:07:44.950 --> 00:07:47.410 align:middle line:84%
Any and all of
those jobs will be

00:07:47.410 --> 00:07:49.780 align:middle line:84%
eliminated from a
human perspective

00:07:49.780 --> 00:07:52.750 align:middle line:84%
and replaced by artificially
intelligent robots

00:07:52.750 --> 00:07:54.860 align:middle line:90%
within 10 years.

00:07:54.860 --> 00:07:59.020 align:middle line:84%
When we're talking about the
singularity eliminating jobs,

00:07:59.020 --> 00:08:01.480 align:middle line:84%
we're talking about
almost any job that

00:08:01.480 --> 00:08:03.640 align:middle line:90%
involves any kind of routine.

00:08:03.640 --> 00:08:08.980 align:middle line:84%
Doctors, lawyers, eliminated,
replaced by AI robots.

00:08:08.980 --> 00:08:11.380 align:middle line:10%
Menial jobs, however,
street sweepers

00:08:11.380 --> 00:08:13.810 align:middle line:10%
and construction workers,
this is the type of job

00:08:13.810 --> 00:08:16.780 align:middle line:10%
that is very difficult
for machines to do.

00:08:16.780 --> 00:08:18.940 align:middle line:10%
Anything that we can
do with our human hands

00:08:18.940 --> 00:08:20.870 align:middle line:10%
and involves
movement in our feet

00:08:20.870 --> 00:08:23.200 align:middle line:10%
are jobs that will
ultimately be secure.

00:08:23.200 --> 00:08:25.060 align:middle line:84%
Thinking jobs,
however, are going

00:08:25.060 --> 00:08:27.190 align:middle line:84%
to be eliminated
on a human basis

00:08:27.190 --> 00:08:29.110 align:middle line:84%
and will be replaced
by machines.

00:08:29.110 --> 00:08:31.780 align:middle line:84%
One of the advantages of
achieving the singularity

00:08:31.780 --> 00:08:33.940 align:middle line:84%
is that it unites
human intelligence

00:08:33.940 --> 00:08:37.690 align:middle line:84%
with machine intelligence
to solve human problems.

00:08:37.690 --> 00:08:40.780 align:middle line:84%
Problems with the environment,
problems with biology,

00:08:40.780 --> 00:08:42.130 align:middle line:90%
problems in medicine.

00:08:42.130 --> 00:08:43.809 align:middle line:10%
If we can solve
these problems, we're

00:08:43.809 --> 00:08:46.960 align:middle line:10%
talking about miraculous
cures for diseases.

00:08:46.960 --> 00:08:49.070 align:middle line:10%
We're talking about
a new way of living.

00:08:49.070 --> 00:08:54.680 align:middle line:10%
But the cost is unparalleled
and beyond our comprehension.

00:08:54.680 --> 00:08:58.010 align:middle line:84%
Artificial intelligence can
have a revolutionary impact

00:08:58.010 --> 00:09:01.610 align:middle line:84%
on our politics, on
medicine, on our environment,

00:09:01.610 --> 00:09:04.580 align:middle line:84%
on biology, because
of its ability

00:09:04.580 --> 00:09:09.230 align:middle line:84%
to access massive amounts of
data and perceive patterns

00:09:09.230 --> 00:09:12.860 align:middle line:84%
that would take perhaps a human
years to be able to perceive.

00:09:12.860 --> 00:09:14.450 align:middle line:84%
So one of the
advantages is being

00:09:14.450 --> 00:09:18.090 align:middle line:84%
able to apply it in medical
diagnosis, for example.

00:09:18.090 --> 00:09:21.860 align:middle line:10%
It can more accurately
diagnose some diseases

00:09:21.860 --> 00:09:25.320 align:middle line:10%
than a medical doctor can,
or certainly a med student.

00:09:25.320 --> 00:09:28.460 align:middle line:10%
So that's one area where it
could have a dramatic impact.

00:09:28.460 --> 00:09:30.950 align:middle line:10%
So where does that
leave the human element?

00:09:30.950 --> 00:09:34.130 align:middle line:10%
Well, if a doctor is
replaced by a robot,

00:09:34.130 --> 00:09:37.180 align:middle line:10%
then maybe a doctor
needs to become a healer

00:09:37.180 --> 00:09:39.260 align:middle line:10%
because a machine
doesn't have empathy

00:09:39.260 --> 00:09:41.930 align:middle line:10%
and a machine can't
offer sympathy

00:09:41.930 --> 00:09:44.690 align:middle line:10%
to a human being on a
human-to-human level.

00:09:44.690 --> 00:09:47.900 align:middle line:10%
So what this will open up
is perhaps a blossoming

00:09:47.900 --> 00:09:49.730 align:middle line:10%
of our true humanity.

00:09:49.730 --> 00:09:53.330 align:middle line:84%
Many of us in menial
jobs, doctors, lawyers,

00:09:53.330 --> 00:09:55.850 align:middle line:84%
not to be insulting, but
they are fairly robotic.

00:09:55.850 --> 00:10:00.320 align:middle line:84%
They make a diagnosis and here's
the prescription for the cure.

00:10:00.320 --> 00:10:02.630 align:middle line:84%
A machine can do that
better than a human.

00:10:02.630 --> 00:10:04.850 align:middle line:84%
An artificially intelligent
computer, we now know,

00:10:04.850 --> 00:10:07.050 align:middle line:84%
is a better doctor
than a human doctor.

00:10:07.050 --> 00:10:10.070 align:middle line:84%
But a human who is a
doctor and a healer

00:10:10.070 --> 00:10:13.240 align:middle line:84%
offers something that a machine
will never be able to offer.

